history.text: Hello?
Are you there?
Yes I am here.
I like the movie. I'm interested in jazz and I appreciate the main character following his passion.
Great thank you
How did you feel about the acting?
Did you enjoy the singing and choreography in the movie?
I thought it was decent acting, although the actors were perhaps not that talented singers or dancers.
I did enjoy the singing and choreography, and the actors did their best given the fact that they are not professionally trained as singers or dancers.
Did you think Ryan Gosling and Emma Stone had good chemistry as co-stars?
Yes, they work well together.
Do you think this movie was deserving of the accolades and hype it received?
Do you agree that the middle of the movie "sags badly"?
I think it is mostly deserving of the praise it received.
I feel like it was a bit too long for me, and for a romantic comedy... but overall I agree that it was enjoyable to watch
It was a great date night movie, and my wife loved it
Did you think John Legend did a good job of acting, considering he is more known as a musician?
I thought he was okay.. I agree that the 3 of them (Gosling, Stone, Legend) were all stretched
John Legend with acting, and the other two with musical performing
I do like him though
Did you find the characters likable?
I did, it was different than most movies I usually watch
How was it different?
I thought it was a nice change of pace with a lot of the other heavy Oscar contending movies
What did you find unique?
I liked how the movie looked, and the feel of Los Angeles as the setting
Do you think any other setting would have suited the movie?
I feel like the homage to Hollywood and California was a big part of it
Maybe Paris?
It reminded me a bit of The Artist, which I really enjoyed a few years back.  It was charming
How do you feel about the ending?
I think it could have worked in another city with an art scene, but I agree that LA is an appropriate setting given Mia's struggles to make it as an actress.
On one had it was sad that Mia and Sebastian did not end up together, but the ending made the movie more interesting and memorable.
And maybe more believable?
In terms of how many people come to be stars and it doesn't work out
And the strain it can put on a relationship when one person becomes more successful than the other
Yes differences in success can put a strain on relationships, when the dynamic changes.
